The '''Chapel of Santisima Virgen de Lujan''' or the '''Chapel of the Blessed Virgin of Lujan'''  ({{lang-es|Capilla de la Santísima Virgen de Luján }}) is a [[Roman Catholic]] [[chapel]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Y2EjAQAAIAAJ|title=Antártida|date=1976-01-01|publisher=Dirección Nacional del Antártico.|language=es}}</ref> located at the Argentine base [[Marambio Base|Marambio]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.todociencia.com.ar/se-funda-en-1969-la-base-aerea-vice-comodoro-marambio-de-la-antartida-argentina/|title=Se funda en 1969 la Base Aérea Vice Comodoro Marambio de la Antártida Argentina {{!}} Todo Ciencia|website=www.todociencia.com.ar|access-date=2016-05-10}}</ref> on [[Seymour Island|Seymour-Marambio Island]] in [[Antarctica]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.waponline.it/ChurchinAntarctica/tabid/65/Default.aspx# |title=Archived copy |access-date=2010-09-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722065855/http://www.waponline.it/ChurchinAntarctica/tabid/65/Default.aspx# |archive-date=2011-07-22 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://es.aleteia.org/2015/07/31/conoce-las-capillas-catolicas-de-la-antartida/|title=Conoce las capillas católicas de la Antártida|last=Pittaro|first=Esteban|date=2015-07-31|website=Aleteia.org {{!}} Español|access-date=2016-05-10}}</ref>  It is one of [[List of Antarctic churches|eight churches on Antarctica]]. The permanent steel-structured chapel is used for Christian worship by the various Argentine personnel on station (as well as visitors).  The chapel features a [[bell tower]] and [[Christian cross|cross]].

