{{Infobox bilateral relations | title = Comoros–France | party1 = Comoros | party2 = France | map = Comoros France Locator.svg | filetype = | size = | mission1 = [[Embassy of Comoros, Paris]] | mission2 = [[Embassy of France, Moroni]] | envoytitle1 = | envoy1 = Ahmed Bourhane | envoytitle2 = | envoy2 = Robby Judes }}
'''Comoros–France''' relations are the [[bilateral relations]] between the [[Union of the Comoros]] and the [[French Republic]].
The Comoros has an embassy in [[Paris]] and France has an embassy in [[Moroni, Comoros|Moroni]]. The Comorian ambassador to France is Ahmed Bourhane.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ambassade-comores.org/|title=Ambassade De L'Union des Comores en France|language=fr|access-date=2 August 2016|publisher=Ambassade des Comores à Paris}}</ref> The French ambassador to Comoros is Robby Judes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ambafrance-km.org/|title=La France en Union des Comores|language=fr|access-date=2 August 2016|publisher=Government of the French Republic}}</ref>
The Comoros and France share a [[maritime border]] via the [[French Southern and Antarctic Lands]]
