{{more citations needed|date=August 2018}} {{Infobox airport | name = Gordil Airport | nativename = | nativename-a = | nativename-r = | image = | image-width = | caption = | IATA = GDI | ICAO = FEGL | type = Private | owner = | operator = | city-served = [[Gordil]], [[Central African Republic]] | location = Melle | elevation-f = 1427 | elevation-m = | coordinates = {{Coord|9|35|00|N|21|44|00|E|type:airport|display=inline,title}} | pushpin_map = Central African Republic | pushpin_label = '''GDI''' | pushpin_map_caption = Location of Gordil Airport in the Central African Republic | website = | metric-elev = | metric-rwy = y | r1-number = 12/30 | r1-length-f = | r1-length-m = 980 | r1-surface = Laterite | stat-year = | stat1-header = | stat1-data = | footnotes = Source: Landings.com<ref name="Landings">[http://aerobaticsweb.org/cgi-bin/search_apt?FEGL Airport record for Melle Gourdil Airport] at Landings.com. Retrieved 2013-08-25</ref> Google Maps<ref>{{cite web |title=Gordil Airport |url=https://www.google.com/maps/@9.58189,21.72662,1312m/data=!3m1!1e3 |website=Google Maps |publisher=Google |accessdate=21 July 2018}}</ref> GCM<ref>{{GCM|GDI|Gordil Airport}}</ref> }}
'''Gordil Airport''' {{airport codes|GDI|FEGL}} is an [[airstrip]] serving [[Gordil]], a village in the [[Vakaga]] prefecture of the [[Central African Republic]]. The airstrip is {{convert|5|km}} southeast of Gordil alongside the RN8 road in the northern part of [[Manovo-Gounda St. Floris National Park]].
The runway is unusable during the rainy season, and aircraft have to do steep departures and landings in order not to disturb the wildlife in the park. The east end of the runway overruns onto the RN8 road.
