{{Infobox bridge | bridge_name = Gorica Bridge | native_name = ''Ura e Goricës'' | native_name_lang = sq | image = Gorica Bridge, Berat.JPG | image_size = 250px | alt = Berat Bridge | caption = | official_name = | other_name = | carries = | crosses = [[Osum|Osum River]] | locale = [[Berat]], [[Albania]] | owner = | maint = | id = | architect = | designer = | engineering = | design = | material = | length = {{convert|129|m|ft|abbr=on}} | width = | height = | mainspan = | spans = | pierswater = | load = | clearance = | below = | life = | builder = | fabricator = | begin = | complete = 1927 | cost = | open = | inaugurated = | toll = | traffic = | preceded = | followed = | heritage = | collapsed = | closed = | replaces = | map_cue = | map_image = | map_alt = | map_text = | map_width = | coordinates = {{coord|40.703|19.944|display=inline,title}} | lat = | long = | references = | extra = }} '''Gorica Bridge''' over the [[Osum]] river is a landmark in the city of [[Berat]], [[Albania]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.unesco.org/events/gorica-bridge-speaks|title=The Gorica Bridge Speaks|work=UNESCO|accessdate=16 November 2015}}</ref>
It is one of the oldest and most popular [[Ottoman empire|Ottoman]] bridges in [[Albania]]. It connects two parts of Berat,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.top-channel.tv/english/artikull.php?id=6712|title=Gorica bridge towards destruction - Top Channel|work=top-channel.tv|accessdate=16 November 2015}}</ref> was originally built from wood in 1780 and was rebuilt with stone in the 1920s.<ref name="argophilia.com">{{cite web|url=http://argophilia.com/albania/bridge-of-gorica.html|title=Bridge of Gorica (Ura e Goricës)|work=argophilia.com|accessdate=16 November 2015}}</ref> The seven-arch bridge is 129 metres (423 ft) long and 5.3 metres (17 ft) wide<ref name="argophilia.com"/> and is built about 10 metres (33 ft) above the average water level. The bridge was renovated in year 2015 by Bashkia Berat (the Municipality of Berat).
According to local legend, the original wooden bridge contained a dungeon in which a girl would be [[incarcerate]]d and starved to appease the spirits responsible for the safety of the bridge.
