{{Infobox language |name=Ngiti |altname=South Lendu |nativename=''Ndruna'' |states=[[Democratic Republic of Congo|Congo (DRC)]] |speakers=100,000 |date=1991 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Nilo-Saharan |fam2=[[Central Sudanic]] |fam3=Eastern |fam4=[[Lendu languages|Lendu]] |iso3=niy |glotto=ngit1239 |glottorefname=Ngiti }} The '''Ngiti''' {{IPAc-en|ə|ŋ|ˈ|ɡ|iː|t|i}},<ref>Laurie Bauer, 2007, ''The Linguistics Student’s Handbook'', Edinburgh</ref> or '''South Lendu''', is an ethnolinguistic group located in the [[Ituri Province]] of the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]]. Ngiti speakers call their language ''Ndruna''. In 1991, the Ngiti numbered 100,000 located in the [[Irumu]] [[Territories of the Democratic Republic of the Congo|territory]] south of [[Bunia]].<ref>[http://www.ethnologue.com/show_language.asp?code=niy Ngiti] from [[Ethnologue]]</ref> During the [[Ituri conflict]], the [[Front for Patriotic Resistance in Ituri]] was formed as a Ngiti militia group and political party.<ref>[http://www.irinnews.org/report.aspx?reportid=53981 "DRC: Who's who in Ituri – militia organisations, leaders"], ''[[IRIN]]'', 20 April 2005</ref>
== Unusual numeral system == [[Ngiti]] is reported to have a [[base-32]] number system with base-4 cycles.<ref>{{ citation | contribution=Rarities in Numeral Systems | first=Harald | last=Hammarström | title=Proceedings of Rara &amp; Rarissima Conference | year=2006 | url=http://www.cs.chalmers.se/~harald2/rarapaper.pdf }}</ref> The following is a list of some Ngiti numerals. {| class="wikitable" border="1" style="text-align:center" ! Number !! Numeral |- ! 1 | atdí |- ! 2 | ɔyɔ |- ! 3 | ɨ̀bhʉ |- ! 4 | ɨ̀fɔ |- ! 8 | àrʉ̀ |- ! 12 | otsi |- ! 16 | ɔpɨ |- ! 20 | àbà |- ! 24 | àròtsí |- ! 28 | àdzòro |- ! 32 | wǎdhɨ̀ |- ! 64 | ɔyɔ wǎdhɨ̀ |- ! 96 | ɨ̀bhʉ wǎdhɨ̀ |- ! 128 | ɨ̀fɔ wǎdhɨ̀ |}
