{{Infobox historic site | name = Palace of Hamza Sultan | native_name = | native_language = | image = | type = | locmapin = | coordinates = <!-- {{Coord}} --> | location = [[Republic of Artsakh]] | built = [[1761]] | architect = | architecture = Arran Architect School | governing_body = | owner = [[Republic of Artsakh]] | caption = | designation1 = | designation1_offname = | designation1_date = | designation1_number = | designation2 = | designation2_offname = | designation2_date = | designation2_number = [http://mct.gov.az/service/lang/az/page/20/nid/4600/ 4227] | designation3 = | designation3_offname = | designation3_date = | designation3_number = | designation4 = | designation4_offname = | designation4_date = | designation4_number = | designation5 = | designation5_offname = | designation5_date = | designation5_number = }} {{Location map many | Republic of Artsakh | relief = yes | width = 300 | lat1_deg = 39.640556 | lon1_deg = 46.409167 | label1 = Palace of Hamza Sultan }}
'''Hamza Sultan palace''' is located in the Husuli village of [[Lachin]] district, [[Azerbaijan]].<ref>[http://karabakhmedia.az/main/7981-qondarma-prezident-saakyan-hemze-sultan-sarayinda-lachindan-son-goruntuler.html karabakhmedia.az]</ref>
Historical documents provide information that palace was erected in the year of 1761. Although the palace was a large complex, only one palace building has remained till the modern period.<ref>[http://www.virtualkarabakh.az/read.php?lang=2&menu=47&id=167#.WVzUVYTyjIU www.virtualkarabakh.az] Karabakh monuments </ref>
The doors and windows of the palace had been made of walnut. Oriental architectural traditions had been widely used in the construction of the building.<ref>[http://www.virtualkarabakh.az/read.php?lang=2&menu=47&id=167#.WVzUVYTyjIU www.virtualkarabakh.az] Karabakh monuments </ref> The palace building had been built of local stones and lime.
