'''Povrateno''' (Macedonian: Повратено; English: ''Returned back'') is a traditional [[Macedonians (ethnic group)|Macedonian]] [[Hora (dance)|''Oro'']], folk dance, from the region of [[Skopje]].

It is a woman dance with medium fast movements on a whole feet. The dancers are holding their belts with left hand over the right one and begin their dance in a position of a half circle. The dance rhythm is 2/4.

==References==
*Dimovski, Mihailo. (1977:66-9). ''Macedonian folk dances (Original in Macedonian: Македонски народни ора)''. Skopje: Naša kniga & Institut za folklor

